Description.TranslatedText: If ADURN is not missing then ADURU='DAYS'
AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date
IF AENDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>AENDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT

Subset to CQ01NAM='' and TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC01FL='Y') within each Subject (Flag First Treatment Emergent Dermatological Event for Time to Event Analysis)
Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC02FL='Y') within each Subject

Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC03FL='Y') within each Subject and SOC

Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC04FL='Y') within each Subject, SOC, and PT
Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCFL='Y') within each Subject

Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCPFL='Y') within each Subject, SOC, and PT

Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCSFL='Y') within each Subject and SOC

AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner. If the day component is missing, a value of '01' is used. If both the month and day are missing no imputation is performed as these dates clearly indicate a start prior to the beginning of treatment. There are no events with completely missing start dates.
ASTDTF='D' if the day value within the character date is imputed. Note that only day values needed to be imputed for this study.
IF ASTDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>ASTDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT

If TRTEMFL='Y' and AEDECOD contains any of the character strings of ('APPLICATION', 'DERMATITIS', 'ERYTHEMA', 'BLISTER') OR if AEBODSYS='SKIN AND SUBCUTANEOUS TISSUE DISORDERS' but AEDECOD is not in ('COLD SWEAT', 'HYPERHIDROSIS', 'ALOPECIA') then CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' Otherwise CQ01NAM=NULL

If ADAE.TRT01A contains 'High' and ADAE.TRTEMFL='Y' then: if ADAE.ASTDT>=start of dose date at Week 24 then ADAE.TRTA='Xanomeline Low Dose' else if ADAE.ASTDT>=start of dose date at Week 2 then ADAE.TRTA=ADAE.TRT01A else if ADAE.ASTDT>=start of dose date at Week 0 then ADAE.TRTA='Xanomeline Low Dose' else if ADAE.TRT01A does not contain 'High' and ADAE.TRTEMFL='Y' then ADAE.TRTA=ADAE.TRT01A

If ADAE.TRT01A contains 'High' and ADAE.TRTEMFL='Y' then: if ADAE.ASTDT>=start of dose date at Week 24 then ADAE.TRTAN=54 else if ADAE.ASTDT>=start of dose date at Week 2 then ADAE.TRTAN=ADAE.TRT01AN else if ADAE.ASTDT>=start of dose date at Week 0 then ADAE.TRTAN=54 else if ADAE.TRT01A does not contain 'High' and ADAE.TRTEMFL='Y' then ADAE.TRTAN=ADAE.TRT01AN
If ASTDT >= TRTSDT > . then TRTEMFL='Y'. Otherwise TRTEMFL='N'

Last observed value for this lab parameter during treatment phase: 'Y' if VISITNUM=12, if subject discontinues prior to VISIT 12, then this variable is set to 'Y' if this is the last assessment of this analyte for the subject
If ALBTRVAL = max(ALBTRVAL) then ANL01FL is 'Y'

Last observed value for this lab parameter during treatment phase: 'Y' if VISITNUM=12, if subject discontinues prior to VISIT 12, then this variable is set to 'Y' if this is the last assessment of this analyte for the subject

If ADLBC.TRT01A contains 'High' and ADLBC.VISIT does not begin with 'UNSCHEDULED' then: if ADLBC.ADT>start of dose date at Week 24 then ADLBC.TRTA='Xanomeline Low Dose' else if ADLBC.ADT>start of dose date at Week 2 then ADLBC.TRTA=ADLBC.TRT01A else ADLBC.TRTA='Xanomeline Low Dose' else if ADLBC.TRT01A does not contain 'High' and ADAE.VISIT does not begin with 'UNSCHEDULED' then ADLBC.TRTA=ADLBC.TRT01A

If ADLBC.TRT01A contains 'High' and ADLBC.VISIT does not begin with 'UNSCHEDULED' then: if ADLBC.ADT>start of dose date at Week 24 then ADLBC.TRTAN=54 else if ADLBC.ADT>start of dose date at Week 2 then ADLBC.TRTAN=ADLBC.TRT01AN else ADLBC.TRTAN=54 else if ADLBC.TRT01A does not contain 'High' and ADAE.VISIT does not begin with 'UNSCHEDULED' then ADLBC.TRTAN=ADLBC.TRT01AN
AGEGR1 = 1 if AGE <65. AGEGR1 = 2 if AGE 65-80. AGEGR1 = 3 if AGE >80.
BMIBLGR1="<25" if . < BMIBL <25. BMIBLGR1="25-<30" if 25 <=BMIBL <30. BMIBLGR1=">=30"if BMIBL >=30.
Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=10 and ENDDT>=date of visit 10, N otherwise
Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=12 and ENDDT>= date of visit 12 , N otherwise
Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=8 and ENDDT >= date of visit 8, N otherwise

For ARMN=0 or 1: CUMDOSE=TRT01PN*TRTDUR. --- For ARMN=2: CUMDOSE will be based on 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 1st dosing interval (i.e., visit4date-TRTSTDT+1 if 1st interval completed, TRTEDT-TRTSTDT+1 if subj discontinued <=visit 4 and > visit 3), 81mg per day for the # of days subj was in 2nd dosing interval (i.e., visit12date-visit4date if 2nd interval completed, TRTEDT-visit4date if subj discontinued <= visit 12 and > visit 4), and 54mg per day for the # of days subj was in 3rd dosing interval (i.e., TRTEDT - visit12date if subj continued after visit 12).
Grouping of DCDECOD values to support summarizing study completion status and reason for discontinuation
MH.MHSTDTC where MHCAT='PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS' converted to SAS date
Y if DCREASCD='Adverse Event'. Null otherwise
number of months between VISIT1DT and DISONSET
Y if SAFFL='Y AND subject has at least one record in QS for ADAS-Cog with VISITNUM>3 AND at least one record in QS for CIBIC+ with VISITNUM>3, N otherwise
COMPLETED if ADSL.DCDECOD='COMPLETED'. DISCONTINUED if ADSL.DCDECOD not equal to COMPLETED.
Y if ARMCD ne ' '. N otherwise
sum of QS.QSORRES values for the subject when QSCAT = MINI-MENTAL STATE
Y if ITTFL='Y' and TRTSDT ne missing. N otherwise
refer to SAP, Section 7.1 - if not pooled then SITEGR1=SITEID. If pooled, SITEGR1 will be 900
If a subject is randomized to the high dose group but does not actually receive any high dose treatment then TRT01A='Xanomeline Low Dose', else TRT01A=ADSL.TRT01P
If a subject is randomized to the high dose group but does not actually receive any high dose treatment then TRT01AN=54, else TRT01AN=ADSL.TRT01PN
Numeric code for TRT01P which corresponds to the randomized dose

The date of final dose (from the CRF) is EX.EXENDTC on the subject's last EX record. If the date of final dose is missing for the subject and the subject discontinued after visit 3, use the date of discontinuation as the date of last dose. Convert the date to a SAS date.
SV.SVSTDTC when SV.VISITNUM=3, converted to SAS date
SV.SVSTDTC when SV.VISITNUM=1, converted to SAS date
if DS.VISITNUM=13 where DSTERM='PROTCOL COMPLETED' then VISNUMEN=12, otherwise VISNUMEN=DS.VISITNUM where DSTERM='PROTCOL COMPLETED'
